  "prompt": "How do I disable screen overlay?",
  "response": "The process to disable screen overlay varies depending on your device and Android version:\n\nFor most Android devices:\n1. Go to Settings\n2. Tap \"Apps\" or \"Application Manager\"\n3. Tap the three-dot menu or \"More\"\n4. Select \"Special access\" or \"Special app access\"\n5. Choose \"Draw over other apps\"\n6. Find the app causing the overlay\n7. Toggle off the permission\n\nFor specific scenarios:\n\u2022 Samsung devices:\n- Settings > Apps > Three-dot menu > Special access > Overlay\n- Or: Settings > Device care > App settings > Overlay\n\n\u2022 Stock Android:\n- Settings > Apps & notifications > Advanced > Special app access > Display over other apps\n\n\u2022 If prompted during app installation:\n- Go to device Settings\n- Find the specific app\n- Disable \"Display over other apps\" permission\n\nTroubleshooting tips:\n- Check which app is causing the overlay\n- Restart your device\n- Uninstall recently installed apps\n- Update your apps and Android version\n\nIf you're experiencing a specific overlay issue, providing more context could help me give more precise instructions.",
